<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC3FFCFFF58FA0016ACC546" blockId="20.[144,759,1422,1566]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFF58FA001646C6FB" box="[144,269,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is an invariable substantive in apposition, which refers to the colloquial name ‘mila’ of my mother (M. A. M.), to whom M. A. M. dedicates this new species as a sign of gratitude for teaching a love of insects.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC3FFCFFF58F9C813CCC22D" blockId="20.[144,759,1605,1903]" lastBlockId="20.[806,1422,198,618]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFF58F9C8161DC503" box="[144,342,1606,1627]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFD16F9C8165AC521" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFD16F9C8165AC521" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be separated easily by the following characters: 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFE8BF90D16AEC5C0" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[323,485,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFE8BF90D16AEC5C0" box="[323,485,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the eye suture 2¥ length of ocellar triangle and 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFDCDF92C1520C5EE" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[517,619,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFDCDF92C1520C5EE" box="[517,619,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
more than 2.5 ¥; 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFF12F94E1635C58D" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[218,382,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFF12F94E1635C58D" box="[218,382,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has all the hairs of mesonotum yellow and 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFEDBF9511638C5AB" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[275,371,1758,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFEDBF9511638C5AB" box="[275,371,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the mesonotum with hairs of two colours, yellow in the anterior and posterior part and a wide transversal band of black hairs in the middle; 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFF3AF8B416D1C417" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[242,410,1850,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFF3AF8B416D1C417" box="[242,410,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the posterior anepisternum mainly yellow and 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFE71F8D71556C436" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[441,541,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFE71F8D71556C436" box="[441,541,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the posterior anepisternum mainly black. 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFBA7FF481271C383" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1135,1338,198,219]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFBA7FF481271C383" box="[1135,1338,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Copestylum milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFABCFF4814ECC3A1" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFABCFF4814ECC3A1" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have sternite 2 and the anterior part of sternite 3 completely yellow but 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFB7BFE8D1212C240" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1203,1369,259,280]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFB7BFE8D1212C240" box="[1203,1369,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has black spots in the middle of these sternites. 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFAE6FEAC14ABC20D" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFAE6FEAC14ABC20D" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Copestylum quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the epandrium in ventral view less than 2¥ as long as broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC3FFCFFCF7FEF31331C132" blockId="20.[806,1422,198,618]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
The early stages of 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFBEDFEF013CEC2CA" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1061,1157,381,403]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFBEDFEF013CEC2CA" box="[1061,1157,381,403]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFABCFEF014EBC2E9" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFABCFEF014EBC2E9" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of spicules on the anterodorsal margin of the mesothorax. Of other Apiciferum group species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFC19FE541379C2B6" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[977,1074,473,495]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFC19FE541379C2B6" box="[977,1074,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC3FFCFFAD8FE54141FC155" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC3FFCFFAD8FE54141FC155" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be separated from it by the AP, which is as long as the TR is wide and the openings of the pupal spiracles clustered on the apex rather than being spread down the sides.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
